        ---------------------------  ENGLISH  -----------------------

        This program permise you to draw pictures with ascii letters,
usefull for logos on a doc for example. A 'picture' takes less than 1900 bytes.
It was developped with STOS basic.
        
        This version is a freeware demo, you should write me for
any suggests and/or comments.
This version is limited to one save, to make you buy my prg ( 30 FF,
about 3 pounds ).

        When the mouse pointer, you can draw. Commands :
space   change ascii code of left mouse button        
B       draw boxes
C       show cursor coordonates
F       fill
P       draw points
V       draw vertical or horizontals lines
=       right button gets left ascii code
F4      load an ascii file ( must have more than 22 lines )
F5      save the picture
F10     put picture in the buffer
UNDO    put buffer on the picture         
ESC     informations ( press F10 before ! )

        It is possible that this prg don't work on STE, it's the fault of
STOS compiler version used. I'll receive the good version in one week...

